<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[806,1422,1545,1905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis box="[806,928,1546,1567]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Discussion</emphasis>
: This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Martin C" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="758 - 763" refId="ref16087" refString="Martin C. 1908. Weldonia parayguensis. Zoologischer Anzeiger 32: 758 - 763." type="journal article" year="1908">Martin (1908)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="1908" box="[940,1123,1577,1598]" class="Turbellaria" family="Stenostomidae" genus="Weldonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Catenulida" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="parayguensis">
<emphasis box="[940,1123,1577,1598]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">W. parayguensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Because this material came from 
<collectingCountry box="[946,1056,1607,1628]" name="Paraguay" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
(South America), the original spelling was corrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus E" box="[1100,1278,1637,1659]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16026" refString="Marcus E. 1945 b. Sobre Microturbelarios do Brasil. Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 1 (25): 1 - 74. Est I - XI." type="journal article" year="1945">Marcus (1945b)</bibRefCitation>
(article 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.254999999999999" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" unit="in" value="32.5">32.5 in</quantity>
the ICZN, 2000).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[806,1422,1545,1905]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luther" authorityYear="1908" baseAuthorityName="Martin" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[831,1015,1699,1720]" class="Catenulida" family="Stenostomidae" genus="Stenostomum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="paraguayense">
<emphasis box="[831,1015,1699,1720]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">S. paraguayense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was placed in the genus 
<taxonomicName class="Catenulida" family="Stenostomidae" genus="Stenostomum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Stenostomum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Luther A" box="[905,1063,1729,1751]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="300" refId="ref15963" refString="Luther A. 1908. Uber Weldonia parayguensis C. H. Martin. Zoologischer Anzeiger 33: 300." type="journal article" year="1908">Luther (1908)</bibRefCitation>
and it was considered as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kennel, 1889" authorityName="Kennel" authorityYear="1889" box="[913,1383,1760,1782]" class="Catenulida" family="Stenostomidae" genus="Stenostomum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Gentianales" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="bicaudatum">
<emphasis box="[913,1216,1760,1781]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="47">Stenostomum bicaudatum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Kennel J" box="[1228,1383,1760,1782]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="447 - 486" refId="ref15547" refString="Kennel J. 1889. Untersuchungen an neuen Turbellarien. Zoologische Jahrbucher Abteilung fur Anatomie der Tiere 3: 447 - 486." type="journal article" year="1889">Kennel, 1889</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nuttycombe J &amp; Waters A" box="[806,1149,1791,1813]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="213 - 301" refId="ref16333" refString="Nuttycombe J, Waters A. 1938. The American species of the genus Stenostomum. American Philosophical Society 79: 213 - 301." type="journal article" year="1938">Nuttycombe &amp; Waters (1938)</bibRefCitation>
. This criterion was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Norena-Janssen C" box="[927,1200,1821,1843]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="211 - 262" refId="ref16197" refString="Norena-Janssen C. 1995. Studies on the taxonomy and ecology of the Turbellaria (Plathelminthes) in the floodplain of the Parana River (Argentina). II. Taxonomy and ecology of the Turbellaria. Archiv fur Hidrobiologie / Supplement Band 107: 211 - 262." type="book chapter" year="1995">Noreña-Janssen (1995)</bibRefCitation>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus E" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16026" refString="Marcus E. 1945 b. Sobre Microturbelarios do Brasil. Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 1 (25): 1 - 74. Est I - XI." type="journal article" year="1945">Marcus (1945b)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Van der Land J" box="[950,1188,1852,1874]" pageId="10" pageNumber="47" pagination="1 - 46" refId="ref16795" refString="Van der Land J. 1970. Kleine Dieren Uit Het Zoete Water Van Suriname Verslag Van Een Onderzoek In 1967. Zoologische Bijdragen 12: 1 - 46." type="journal article" year="1970">Van der Land (1970)</bibRefCitation>
recognize the validity of both species.
</paragraph>
